---
layout: layout.njk
title: registry.0x0.sk — brutalist ledger
---
<section class="hero">
  <div>
    <h2>Claim your slice of the void</h2>
    <p>
      This ledger lists every assigned <strong>0x0.sk</strong> subdomain. Some
      records stay private through SHA-256 hashes, but availability is always
      transparent.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="hero__cta">
    <p>Need one? Reach out via <a href="https://ko-fi.com/D1D5DMOTA">Ko-fi</a>.</p>
    <p class="note">Emoji welcome. Private picks stay hashed.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="search" aria-labelledby="search-title">
  <div>
    <h3 id="search-title">Is your subdomain free?</h3>
    <p>
      Type a name, hit enter, and we will cross-check both raw and hashed
      records—no toggles, no fuss.
    </p>
  </div>
  <form id="search-form" novalidate>
    <label for="query">subdomain</label>
    <div class="input-row">
      <input
        id="query"
        name="query"
        type="text"
        placeholder="meow"
        autocomplete="off"
        spellcheck="false"
        required
      />
      <button type="submit">check</button>
    </div>
    <p class="hint">We normalize emoji → punycode and auto-append .0x0.sk.</p>
  </form>
</section>

<section class="result" aria-live="polite">
  <div id="result-card" class="card">
    <p class="status muted">Start typing to see availability.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="ledger" aria-label="Known registrations">
  <header>
    <h3>Visible subdomains</h3>
    <p>Hashes stay hidden, but these entries are public.</p>
  </header>
  <ul class="grid">
    {% for domain in subdomains %}
      {% if "." in domain %}
        <li>{{ domain }}</li>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
</section>

<script id="subdomain-data" type="application/json">{{ subdomains | dump | safe }}</script>
